<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Recruiting/209:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Capetown</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Denby</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17T18:00:00-05:00">April
                                        17, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. For the Minister. Your 37, April 10, 4 p.m. South African
                                Minister discussed this matter on March 10 with Department<note n="10" xml:id="d387fn10">Memorandum by the Chief of the Special
                                    Division, dated March 10, 1941, not printed.</note> which
                                informed him that it has in principle no objection but that matter
                                would have to be considered in connection with national defense
                                needs. Minister was then referred to American Red Cross with which
                                he is understood to be continuing conversations.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>